<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 3151/90 of 29 October 1990 on stepping up checks in Portugal on expenditure charged to the Guarantee Section of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 3151/90 P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust finantseeritavate kulude kontrolli tugevdamise kohta Portugalis 29. oktoober 1990 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 8 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2048/88 (4), the Member States are to take the measures necessary to satisfy themselves that transactions financed by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF) are actually carried out and are executed correctly, to prevent and deal with irregularities and to recover sums lost as a result of irregularities or negligence; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (3) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2048/88) (4) artikli 8 alusel peavad liikmesriigid v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid veendumaks, et Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondist (EAGGF) rahastatavad toimingud toimuvad tegelikult ja n&otilde;uetekohaselt, selleks et t&otilde;kestada ja k&auml;sitleda eeskirjade eiramist ning sisse n&otilde;uda eeskirjade eiramise v&otilde;i hooletuse tagaj&auml;rjel kaotatud summad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas on 1 January 1991 financing by the EAGGF Guarantee Section will extend in Portugal to products subject to transition by stages and the tasks incumbent on the departments responsible for controls and authorized to pay expenditure in that Member State will be considerably greater as a result; </inglise>
<eesti> 1. jaanuarist 1991 h&otilde;lmab EAGGF tagatisrahastust rahastamine Portugalis tooteid, mille suhtes kehtib etapiviisiline &uuml;leminek, ning seet&otilde;ttu suureneb k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis kontrollimise eest vastutavate ja kulude tasumiseks volitatud asutuste kohustuste maht m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Instituto Nacional de Interven&atilde;ao e Garantia Agr&Icirc;cola (INGA) has been designated by the Portuguese Government in accordance with Article 4 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 to effect payment of most of the expenditure referred to in Articles 2 and 3 of that Regulation and in addition to ensure the coordination and processing of data concerning all expenditure, including expenditure the payment of which is actually effected by other authorities designated for the purpose; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklile 4 m&auml;&auml;ras Portugali valitsus Instituto Nacional de Interven&ccedil;&atilde;o e Garantia Agr&iacute;cola (INGA) suurema osa nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklites 2 ja 3 nimetatud maksete teostajaks ning lisaks sellele peab nimetatud asutus tagama k&otilde;iki kulusid (sealhulgas kulusid, mille tasuvad muud selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud asutused) k&auml;sitlevate andmete koordineerimise ja t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise. </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the INGA does not have sufficient data-processing infrastructure to ensure the optimum collection, processing, checking and transmission of all data on expenditure financed by the EAGGF Guarantee Section; whereas such a shortcoming is likely to hamper the sound management, checks and the prevention of irregularities and fraud; </inglise>
<eesti> INGA-l puudub k&otilde;igi EAGGF tagatisrahastust finantseeritavate kuludega seotud andmete optimaalse kogumise, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise, kontrollimise ja edastamise tagamiseks piisav andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluse infrastruktuur; niisugune puudus v&otilde;ib takistada t&otilde;husat majandamist ja kontrollimist ning eeskirjade eiramise ja pettuste v&auml;ltimist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the INGA has drawn up a project to make good that shortcoming and in view of the costs has requested that the Community contribute financially towards its implementation, </inglise>
<eesti> INGA on koostanud k&otilde;nealuse puuduse parandamiseks kava ning taotleb kulusid arvestades, et &uuml;hendus annaks rahalise panuse projekti rakendamisse, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A Community contribution shall be granted to Portugal to enable it to set up a data-processing system in the Instituto Nacional de Interven&atilde;ao e Garantia Agr&Icirc;cola and links other paying and monitoring agencies. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus toetab Portugali rahaliselt, et see saaks rajada Instituto Nacional de Interven&ccedil;&atilde;o e Garantia Agr&iacute;cola andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluss&uuml;steemi ning luua &uuml;henduse muude makse- ja kontrollasutustega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The data-processing system referred to in paragraph 1 must permit the collection, processing, monitoring and transmission to the Commission of data on expenditure financed by the EAGGF Guarantee Section in Portugal. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluss&uuml;steem peab v&otilde;imaldama EAGGF tagatisrahastust Portugalis rahastatavate kuludega seotud andmete kogumist, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist, kontrollimist ja komisjonile edastamist. </eesti>
<inglise> It must relate in particular to the sound management and the effectiveness of checks and the prevention of irregularities and fraud which may be committed to the detriment of the EAGGF. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle s&uuml;steemi eesm&auml;rk on eelk&otilde;ige tagada veatu majandamine ja kontrolli t&otilde;husus ning v&auml;ltida eeskirjade eiramist ja pettusi, mis v&otilde;iksid kahjustada EAGGFi. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community financial contribution may not exceed 70 % of the expenditure actually incurred in the establishment and commissioning of the data-processing system referred to in paragraph 1 and must not exceed ECU 4 million in total. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse panus l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluss&uuml;steemi rajamise ja kasutuselev&otilde;tmisega seotud tegelike kulude finantseerimisse ei tohi olla suurem kui 70% ja selle kogusumma ei tohi &uuml;letada 4 miljonit ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community financial contribution may be the subject of advance instalments. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse rahalise panuse v&otilde;ib maksta avansiliste osamaksetena. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of applying Article 1 (3), the ECU 4 million shall be converted into Portuguese escudos by applying the exchange rate in force on the penultimate working day of the month preceding that during which the balance is paid, and published in the 'C' series of the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaldamiseks arvestatakse 4 miljonit ek&uuml;&uuml;d &uuml;mber Portugali eskuudodesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teataja C-seerias avaldatud vahetuskursi j&auml;rgi, mis kehtib saldo maksmisele eelneva kuu eelviimasel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed rules for implementing this Regulation shall be adopted as the need arises in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajaduse korral v&otilde;etakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 29 October 1990. </inglise>
